    "description": {
      "value": "<strong>Investigator Talents</strong><br/><br/><p>The ability reduction of the investigator's anathemas increases to 10, and he adds DR/- and regeneration to the list of abilities he can lower with an anathema. In addition, when an investigator creates an anathema, he can designate a specific kind of creature (such as vampires) in addition to the creature type. When used against this specific foe, the DC of the save against the anathema is 2 higher than the component poison. An investigator must have the anathema investigator talent to select this talent.</p>",
